{
  "description": "A breathtaking panoramic view of Yosemite Valley, dominated by towering granite cliffs and lush greenery. El Capitan stands prominently on the left, a massive vertical rock formation. Opposite it, Half Dome rises majestically, its distinctive shape carved by glaciers. A thin, white ribbon of water cascades down a cliff face, forming Yosemite Falls, visible in the center of the valley. The valley floor is densely covered with a vibrant green forest of coniferous trees, creating a stark contrast with the gray and brown hues of the granite. Patches of snow cling to the upper reaches of the cliffs and distant mountains. The sky is overcast with muted gray and white clouds, providing a soft, diffused light. The overall composition creates a sense of scale and grandeur, emphasizing the power and beauty of nature.",
